com.b2international.snowowl.datastore.server.cdo

Class AbstractCDOConflictProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.snowowl.datastore.server.cdo.AbstractCDOConflictProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICDOConflictProcessor
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NullCDOConflictProcessor, SnomedCDOConflictProcessor

    public abstract class AbstractCDOConflictProcessor
extends Object
implements ICDOConflictProcessor
    Abstract superclass for ICDOConflictProcessors that only want to report a subset of possible application-level conflicts.

      • addedInSource

        public Object addedInSource(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.CDORevision sourceRevision,
                            Map<org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.id.CDOID,Object> targetMap)
        Checks if the specified CDORevision from the source change set conflicts with any changes on the target.

        The default case will allow the add by returning sourceRevision (a CDORevision).

        Specified by:
        addedInSource in interface ICDOConflictProcessor
        Parameters:
        sourceRevision - the new CDORevision from the source change set
        targetMap - the computed change set for the target branch, indexed by CDOID
        Returns:
        • null if the add should be ignored;
        • a CDORevision if an addition should take place;
        • a CDOID if an object should be removed;
        • a DefaultCDOMerger.Conflict if a merge conflict should be reported.

        Checks if the specified CDOFeatureDelta from the target change set conflicts with the corresponding CDOFeatureDelta on the source.

        The default case implements the same behavior as DefaultCDOMerger.PerFeature.

        Specified by:
        changedInSourceAndTargetSingleValued in interface ICDOConflictProcessor
        Parameters:
        targetFeatureDelta - the single-value change on the target
        sourceFeatureDelta - the single-value change on the source
        Returns:
        • null if a conflict should be reported;
        • a CDOFeatureDelta containing the "winning" change otherwise.

      • changedInTargetAndDetachedInSource

        public Object changedInTargetAndDetachedInSource(org.eclipse.emf.cdo.common.revision.delta.CDORevisionDelta targetDelta)
        Checks if the object with the removed CDOID from the target change set conflicts with an item in the source change set.

        The default case will check if the change did not involve releasing the component, and if so, reports a conflict; allows the removal otherwise.

        Specified by:
        changedInTargetAndDetachedInSource in interface ICDOConflictProcessor
        Parameters:
        targetDelta - the computed change on the target branch for the object removed on the source branch
        Returns:
        • null if the add should be ignored;
        • a CDORevision if an addition should take place;
        • a CDOID if an object should be removed;
        • a DefaultCDOMerger.Conflict if a merge conflict should be reported.
